132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1338
H.P. 873 House of Representatives, March 27, 2025
Resolve, Directing State Agencies and Semiautonomous State
Agencies to Provide a List of Surplus Properties and Properties
Eligible for Redevelopment to the Maine Redevelopment Land Bank
Authority
Reference to the Committee on Housing and Economic Development suggested and
ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative SACHS of Freeport.
Cosponsored by Senator CURRY of Waldo and
Representatives: Speaker FECTEAU of Biddeford, GERE of Kennebunkport, GOLEK of
Harpswell, JULIA of Waterville, MALON of Biddeford, ROBERTS of South Berwick,
YUSUF of Portland, Senator: BAILEY of York.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Sec. 1. Surplus property identified for redevelopment. Resolved: That, by
2 October 1, 2025, each state agency and semiautonomous state agency shall submit to the
3 Maine Redevelopment Land Bank Authority, established in the Maine Revised Statutes,
4 Title 30-A, section 5154 and referred to in this section as "the authority," a list of properties
5 owned by the agency that the agency has determined to be surplus and potentially eligible
6 for redevelopment under Title 30-A, section 5157. The authority shall provide to each
7 agency the information that must be included for each property identified on the agency's
8 list. By December 3, 2025, the authority shall submit a report to the Joint Standing
9 Committee on Housing and Economic Development. The report must include the
10 authority's findings regarding the listed properties and the potential for redevelopment of
11 those properties, including redevelopment for housing and economic development
12 purposes. For the purposes of this section, "semiautonomous state agency" has the same
13 meaning as in Title 5, section 1972, subsection 9.
14 SUMMARY
1155 This resolve requires each state agency and each agency created by an act of the
1166 Legislature that is not a part of the Executive Department to submit to the Maine
1177 Redevelopment Land Bank Authority a list of properties owned by the agency that the
1188 agency has determined to be surplus and potentially eligible for redevelopment under the
1199 Maine Revised Statutes, Title 30-A, section 5157. It also requires the Maine
2200 Redevelopment Land Bank Authority to submit a report to the Joint Standing Committee
2211 on Housing and Economic Development regarding the properties and their potential for
2222 redevelopment.
